          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2018-10-15T22:11:02Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p>This bill prohibits the use of any federal funds by the National Science Foundation to study:</p> <ul> <li>how Members of Congress set priorities within the constraints of the contemporary legislature;</li> <li>the relationship between Members in the sharing of guidance and informative documents; or </li> <li>the impact of such guidance and documents, including dear colleague letters, sent between Members. </li> </ul>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2018-05-09T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
      </billSummaries>
    </summaries>
    <title>To prohibit the National Science Foundation from conducting certain studies on relationships between Members of Congress with respect to the sharing of guidance and informative documents.</title>
